Letter to Kim Jong Il from C.C. of NDFSK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il received a letter from the Central Committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea on April 15, the Day of the Sun.
 Noting that President Kim Il Sung provided the guiding idea of the times by founding the immortal Juche idea, performed unparalleled exploits in liberating the country and defending the sovereignty of the nation by defeating the two most ferocious imperialist formidable enemies and set a world-wide example of creation and construction by leading the social reform and socialist construction at different stages to victory and turning the north into a powerful socialist state, independent in politics, self-supporting in the economy and self-reliant in national defence, the letter added that all this represents the greatest exploits to be specially recorded in human history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The president who worked heart and soul for national reunification, always considerate of the people in the south, laid down the wisest line and policy of national reunification and led all the Koreans to the road of independence and unity, providing a solid groundwork for the independent and peaceful reunification of the country, the letter said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pointing out that the cause of Juche started by the president is being creditably carried forward and developed by Kim Jong Il, the letter continued: He most successfully accomplished the cause of perpetuating the memory of the president, thus enabling the people to hold him in high esteem as they did in his lifetime and giving a steady continuity to his revolutionary history. This is the greatest exploit as he paved the way for creditably carrying forward the revolutionary cause and winning an eternal victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The president's last instruction on national reunification is being successfully carried out and the cause of building a prosperous powerful nation is making a leaping advance thanks to the endless journey for Songun guidance made by Kim Jong Il. He is the most outstanding leader of the present era and the bright sun of the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will decisively foil the U.S. moves to provoke a war and bring earlier the day of independent reunification by further intensifying the movement for reunification through national cooperation under the uplifted banner of the three charters for national reunification and the June 15 joint declaration and thus realize his life-long desire.

Schoolchildren's camping begins 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- The first camping this year started at the schoolchildren's camps across the country on the occasion of the day of the sun.
 A ceremony of receiving campers was held at the Mangyongdae Schoolchildren's Camp on April 15. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the ceremony were Ryang Man Gil, chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee, Choe Yong Gu, secretary of the central committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, and officials concerned and teachers of the camp and campers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A report and speeches were made at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers said that schoolchildren would enjoy the first-term camping in the place associated with the immortal revolutionary history of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They hoped that always remembering the loving care shown by Kim Jong Il for the campers, they would find their days at the camp meaningful, training their bodies and minds and consolidating what they have learned through various activities such as mountaineering and excursion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called on all the campers to earnestly learn from the childhood of the president and Kim Jong Il during the camping and thus become dependable builders of the country, knowledgeable, virtuous and healthy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Similar ceremonies took place at the Songdowon International Schoolchildren's Camp, Myohyangsan Schoolchildren's Mountaineering Camp, the Sokam Schoolchildren's Camp, the Sohungho Schoolchildren's Camp, the Kaesong Schoolchildren's Camp, the South Hwanghae Provincial Schoolchildren's Camp and other camps.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from Chongryon 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il received a letter from the central standing committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) on April 15 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 The letter said that President Kim Il Sung is the eternal sun of Juche, father of socialist Korea and the benefactor who helped the Koreans in Japan to be reborn. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that all the Chongryon officials and Koreans in Japan significantly commemorating the day of the sun are firmly determined to pave with pride the way for the movement of Koreans in Japan in the new century under the leadership of Kim Jong Il as the president wished in his lifetime, the letter renewed their pledge to more firmly strengthen Chongryon into the single-hearted ranks full of the faith that only victory is in store for the country and the nation and the movement as long as they are under the leadership of Kim Jong Il and unite close broad strata of compatriots on the road of patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No matter how tense the international situation may remain due to the imperialists' high-handed practices, we will protect the DPRK, genuine motherland of the Koreans in Japan, to the last and make a tangible contribution to the building of a great prosperous power, the letter concluded.

Reception given for participants of April Spring Friendship Art Festival 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- The Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly hosted a reception for the participants of the 21st April Spring Friendship Art Festival at the People's Palace of Culture on Tuesday evening on the occasion of the Day of the Sun, the birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung.
 Present on invitation were foreign delegations and delegates, artistes and overseas Korean artistes participating in the festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were premier of the DPRK cabinet Hong Song Nam, vice-President of the SPA Presidium Yang Hyong Sop, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea Jong Ha Chol, chairman of the festival organizing committee Jang Chol, Minister of Culture Kang Nung Su, chief secretary of the cabinet Jong Mun San, chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee Ryang Man Gil, vice-chairmen of the festival organizing committee and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A speech was made there.

Solution to Korean nuclear issue depends on U.S. attitude 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- Minju Joson today comments on the fact that most of member states of the un security council opposed the U.S. stand at its closed meeting held on April 9, asserting that the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula should be peacefully settled between the DPRK and the U.S.
 The news analyst says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The outcome of the meeting represents a relatively fair and objective assessment of the two conflicting stands of the DPRK and the U.S. on the nuclear issue of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The nuclear issue is a matter between the DPRK and the U.S. in every sense and it, therefore, can be settled peacefully only through the DPRK-U.S. dialogue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is possible to settle the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula if the U.S. sincerely gives up its hostile will and honestly approaches dialogue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present reality urgently requires the U.S. to drop its unreasonable and wrong assertion as early as possible and opt for a peaceful solution to the nuclear issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will not stick to any particular dialogue format if the U.S. has a will to make a brave switchover in its policy toward the DPRK to settle the issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A solution to the issue hinges on what is the real intention of the U.S.

Greetings to Syrian President
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA)--General Secretary Kim Jong Il today sent a message of greetings to Bashar al Assad, General Secretary of the Central Committee of the Arab Socialist Baath Party and President of Syria, on the occasion of the 57th anniversary of its independence.
 The message extended warm congratulations to the president and, through him, to the friendly Syrian government and people on this occasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Since the independence the Syrian people have achieved many successes in the struggle to defend the sovereignty of the country and the nation and build prosperous Syria under the correct leadership of the party, the message said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people always extend full support to the president and the people of Syria in their just cause to achieve the progress and modernization of the country, retake the occupied Arab territories including Golan Heights and seek a fair and comprehensive solution to the Mid-East problem. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message expressed belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would grow stronger and develop and wished the president good health and happiness.

Kim Jong Il enjoys art performance of KPA Merited Chorus
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il together with servicepersons, enjoyed an art performance given by the KPA Merited Chorus "the Song of Korea Sung Through Generations" on April 15, the Day of the Sun.
 Among the audience were chief of the KPA General Staff Kim Yong Chun, Minister of the People's Armed Forces Kim Il Chol, secretaries of the WPK Central Committee Kim Kuk Thae, Kim Yong Sun and Kim Ki Nam and senior officials of the party and the army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Put on the stage were famous songs "Green Pine Standing on Nam Hill", "the Song of Korea", "Nostalgia", "Dear General, Where are You", "Korea, I will Glorify Thee" and other chorus numbers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers truthfully represented the high national pride and the strong self-confidence of the Korean people blessed with the illustrious leaders generation after generation and the proud path of victory and glory they have covered under the wise leadership of President Kim Il Sung, father of socialist Korea. They also clearly manifested the firm faith and will and militant mettle of the army and people to devotedly defend the headquarters of the revolution, holding higher the red flag of the revolution despite whatever difficulty and ordeal, and accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche, true to the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The audience was deeply impressed by the performance great in ideological value and artistic merits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il expressed great satisfaction at the successful performance given by the artistes of the chorus replete with the revolutionary spirit of Mt. Paektu and that of soldiers. He expressed expectation and belief that they would more powerfully encourage the army and the people in their sacred struggle to eternally glorify the immortal revolutionary exploits of the president.
